last_episode_to_air.name: Bonafide Heroes
last_episode_to_air.overview: Kirk Manlord, the host of a sleazy reality show Bonafide Heroes about universe's heroes, does a piece on Duck Dodgers. The crew follows Duck 24/7 and interviews his enemies and friends. Dodgers decides to use this opportunity to promote himself.

name: Duck Dodgers
overview: Duck Dodgers is an American animated television series, based on the 1953 theatrical cartoon short Duck Dodgers in the 24½th Century, produced by Warner Bros.
tagline: If he's our future, we're history.

episodes.name: Duck Deception
episodes.overview: Dodgers accidentally explodes the ship's energy core, sending the crew adrift. To convince a Martian ship to rescue them, Dodgers dresses Cadet as a space vixen/Dodgers must escort a beautiful secret agent to a Martian-controlled planet. To prove his love for the lady spy, Dodgers volunteers to destroy an enemy radio tower.

episodes.name: The Spy Who Didn't Love Me
episodes.overview: With a new robot on his crew, Agent Roboto, Dodgers discovers he has a crew member who will do whatever he says. Unfortunately, when Agent Roboto is a little too good at saving the day, Dodgers plans to get rid of his newfound crew member/Cadet makes a bet with the Queen of Mars that Dodgers can race the Martian Commander in a hot-rod space race and win. Dodgers begins by cheating but will it be enough to win?

episodes.name: The Fowl Friend
episodes.overview: Dodgers and Cadet are put on trial for destroying Earth's defensive shield, and is being persecuted by Capt. Star Johnson/Dodgers responds to a planet's distress signal and mistakes its gelatinous inhabitants for the enemy invaders.

episodes.name: The Fast and the Feathery
episodes.overview: Dodgers and Cadet come into contact with a flower that induces rapid aging. To obtain the cure, they must head to an enemy planet, where they discover the flower reverses aging on Martians/Dodgers and Cadet must retrieve a baby philosopher to save a peace conference. When Martians kidnap the baby, Cadet gives chase while Dodgers disguises himself as the baby to prevent war.

episodes.name: The Trial of Duck Dodgers
episodes.overview: A fat-sucking space vampire hypnotizes Dodgers into detaining Cadet for a pork dinner. But having discovered the vampire's one weakness, health food, Cadet makes a decoy of himself from tofu/Drake Darkstar, an evil Duck Dodgers doppelganger, steals Dodgers' identity to escape incarceration. When Dodgers escapes from prison and arrives on his own spaceship, he must prove to Cadet that he is the real Duck Dodgers.

episodes.name: Big Bug Mamas
episodes.overview: A rebel army of gophers vows to overtake Mars. Marvin's canine companion discovers the plan during a golf game but can't communicate the information to his master. Without Marvin's help, it's up to K-9 to save the planet on his own/Dodgers and Cadet investigate space barbarians planning to invade Earth. While on the rogue planet, Cadet discovers a shiny rock that transforms him into a gargantuan warrior.

episodes.name: Duck Codgers
episodes.overview: Space pirates use a disappearo device to render their ship invisible. After they wreak havoc, Dodgers and Cadet must disguise as pirates to claim the disappearo device for Earth before the Martian Commander claims it for Mars.

episodes.name: Where's Baby Smartypants?
episodes.overview: Dodgers drags Cadet along to Robo-World, a space vacation fantasy theme park, where Nasty Canasta, an intergalactic bounty hunter, creates trouble for Dodgers and the Cadet/Marvin kidnaps Dodgers and steals his brain, replacing it with a high tech gizmo that everyone mistakes for a fancy hat. Dodgers is assigned to track down the stolen brain, unaware that it belongs to him.

episodes.name: I'm Going to Get You, Fat Sucka
episodes.overview: Due to a mistake, Dodgers gets a Green Lantern uniform instead of his own. Donning the garment, mask and ring, Dodgers gains Green Lantern powers. Then, the continuation of the story where Dodgers must thwart the wicked Sinestro's plan.

episodes.name: Detained Duck
episodes.overview: Obsessed with ruining Dodgers' career, Marvin goes back in time to foil the college football exploits of his nemesis only to learn Dodgers must be schooled in his own field of alleged expertise/Because Dodgers has been such a worthy adversary to the Queen and X-2, the Queen decides to take Dodgers as her King, if he can pass three death-defying Martian trials: Combat, Endurance, and Logic.

episodes.name: K-9 Kaddy
episodes.overview: Hollywood mogul Harry Vermin lures Dodgers into a trap by offering to produce the duck's life story. Dodgers is made into a star after he his cast as the lead in his self-titled movie. X-2 is really behind it, and he has hired an assassin to play Dodgers' female Cadet.

episodes.name: Pig of Action
episodes.overview: After being humiliated by Dodgers for rejecting her offer of King of Mars, the Queen kidnaps Cadet in an all-out attempt to exact revenge on Dodgers, who abandoned her at the wedding altar/

episodes.name: Shiver Me Dodgers
episodes.overview: Dodgers must keep his Protectorate Captain's certification by taking a yearly course. He encounters a tough space academy drill sergeant and his own disdain for authority in the process/Tired of mounting space hijinks, Dodgers quits the Protectorate to work in the food service industry. Although he's trying to get away from everything, he's constantly reminded about everything from his past while working at the restaurant.

episodes.name: They Stole Dodgers' Brain
episodes.overview: Marvin kidnaps Dodgers and steals his brain, replacing it with a high tech gizmo that everyone mistakes for a fancy hat. Dodgers is assigned to track down the stolen brain, unaware that it belongs to him.

episodes.name: The Wrath of Canasta
episodes.overview: Dodgers drags Cadet along to Robo-World, a space vacation fantasy theme park, where Nasty Canasta, an intergalactic bounty hunter, creates trouble for Dodgers and the Cadet.

episodes.name: The Green Loontern
episodes.overview: Due to a mistake, Dodgers gets a Green Lantern uniform instead of his own. Donning the garment, mask and ring, Dodgers gains Green Lantern powers. Then, the continuation of the story where Dodgers must thwart the wicked Sinestro's plan.

episodes.name: Quarterback Quack
episodes.overview: Obsessed with ruining Dodgers' career, Marvin goes back in time to foil the college football exploits of his nemesis only to learn Dodgers must be schooled in his own field of alleged expertise.

episodes.name: To Love a Duck
episodes.overview: Because Dodgers has been such a worthy adversary to the Queen and X-2, the Queen decides to take Dodgers as her King, if he can pass three death-defying Martian trials: Combat, Endurance, and Logic.

episodes.name: Hooray for Hollywood Planet
episodes.overview: Hollywood mogul Harry Vermin lures Dodgers into a trap by offering to produce the duck's life story. Dodgers is made into a star after he his cast as the lead in his self-titled movie. X-2 is really behind it, and he has hired an assassin to play Dodgers' female Cadet.

episodes.name: The Queen is Wild
episodes.overview: After being humiliated by Dodgers for rejecting her offer of King of Mars, the Queen kidnaps Cadet in an all-out attempt to exact revenge on Dodgers, who abandoned her at the wedding altar.

episodes.name: Back to the Academy
episodes.overview: Dodgers must keep his Protectorate Captain's certification by taking a yearly course. He encounters a tough space academy drill sergeant and his own disdain for authority in the process.

episodes.name: Enemy Yours
episodes.overview: Once Dodgers finds out that X-2 doesn't think of him as his arch enemy, but just as a mild annoyance, Jealous that Marvin has another arch enemy, Dodgers involves himself in Marvin's skirmish with the dreaded Dr. Woe.

episodes.name: Duck Departure
episodes.overview: Tired of mounting space hijinks, Dodgers quits the Protectorate to work in the food service industry. Although he's trying to get away from everything, he's constantly reminded about everything from his past while working at the restaurant.

episodes.name: Pig Planet
episodes.overview: Dodgers and Cadet visit Cadet's home planet, Swinus Nine, to quell the cruel reign of his evil cousin Zag. Cadet is about to be married to his designated life partner in order to assume the throne when Zag kidnaps the bride!

episodes.name: Invictus Interruptus
episodes.overview: Dodgers and Cadet must slow down the Invictus, an awesome new Martian space destroyer, so that Star Johnson can engage it in battle. Things do not go as planned when Dodgers opts for a risky preemptory attack/Dodgers demands a pet and settles on a cute, fuzzy little Energy Mutator alien creature. However, sending it through the ship's evaporator causes a molecular change in the animal that bodes ill for Dodgers, Cadet and the ship.

episodes.name: Pet Peeved
episodes.overview: Dodgers and Cadet help Rickki Roundhouse, a robotic child hero of the planet Nippano, battle the normally docile Maninsuit monster, who is suddenly wreaking global havoc due to forces unknown!/Marvin and his faithful Martian companion, K-9, go on a hunting trip only to find themselves the hunted by a formidable, mysterious alien adversary.

episodes.name: The Menace of Maninsuit
episodes.overview: To impress the Lady Zorga and win an intergalactic talent contest, Dodgers attempts to borrow the greatest singing voice of all time, the velvet pipes of Mr. Tom Jones!/Dodgers unfreezes Baby-faced Moonbeam, a 300-plus-year-old arch villain who resembles a little boy. Dodgers regards the intergalactic miscreant as his son despite Babyface's escalating evil deeds.

episodes.name: K-9 Quarry
episodes.overview: Dodgers is surprised to learn he has a new female cadet, and he is equally shocked to find that she harbors an escalating, twisted obsession with him/Angling to make a profit by converting his ship into a luxury space liner, Dodgers gets blindsided by a Martian attack while carrying tourists. It's up to Dodgers and Cadet to battle while keeping the paying passengers entertained.

episodes.name: Talent Show a Go-Go
episodes.overview: A mysterious scourge strikes members of the Protectorate. It spreads to Earth and then to Mars leaving only Dodgers, Cadet and Marvin oddly untouched. It's up to them to reverse the plague's distinctive physical and mental effects.

episodes.name: The Love of a Father
episodes.overview: A swashbuckling Dodgers and Cadet try to help a poor village by confronting the villain Hilgalgo and his sidekick Vasquez/Whilst on their way to a golfing holiday, Dodgers, Cadet and I.Q. Hi battle both the paranormal and their own paranoia onboard Dodger's haunted ship.

episodes.name: The New Cadet
episodes.overview: Masativo, a living crystal planet annoyed with interlopers like Dodgers destroying the asteroids it needs to survive, pits Dodgers against Taz in hand-to-hand combat to the death/Whilst stranded at an Intergalactic Space Airport, I.Q. Hi and the Martian Queen reminisce about Dodgers' fabled exploits and wonders if he maybe isn't as dumb as he seems.

episodes.name: The Love Duck
episodes.overview: Dodgers and Cadet join a band of mythical adventurers in an online game to defeat the wicked sorceress Lezah and rescue a beautiful princess. However, things aren’t as they seem in virtual reality/Intent on proving he's a born farmer, Dodgers takes charge of running the hydroponic space farm aboard his vessel. But to eradicate one annoying weed, Dodgers introduces a Martian cure far worse than the problem.

episodes.name: The Fudd
episodes.overview: Dodgers transports an intergalactic singing star, Lady Chanticleer, to the Fluoride Festival of Festoovius Five, taking tons of abuse from the perfectionist diva/I.Q. Hi makes the mistake of leaving Dodgers alone with his ancestor's castle, and so Dodgers tells I.Q. Hi what happened in a Frankenstein-type exaggeration.

episodes.name: The Mark of Xero
episodes.overview: When his status as Surf King on an all-beach planet is wiped out by the Crusher, Dodgers must prevail in an impossible surfing contest/

episodes.name: I See Duck People
episodes.overview: When Dodgers brings Earth and Mars to the brink of war, Dodgers betrays Cadet by letting him take the blame for Dodgers' offense, landing the young pig in space prison.

episodes.name: Deathmatch Duck
episodes.overview: The treaty signing does not go smoothly, and Dodgers finally realizes he must restore his friendship with Cadet by clearing Cadet's name. They join forces with Marvin to capture Z9, who kidnapped the Martian Queen in a grab for power.

episodes.name: Deconstructing Dodgers
episodes.overview: Whilst stranded at an Intergalactic Space Airport, I.Q. Hi and the Martian Queen reminisce about Dodgers' fabled exploits and wonders if he maybe isn't as dumb as he seems.

episodes.name: M.M.O.R.P.D.
episodes.overview: Dodgers and Cadet join a band of mythical adventurers in an online game to defeat the wicked sorceress Lezah and rescue a beautiful princess. However, things aren’t as they seem in virtual reality.

episodes.name: Old McDodgers
episodes.overview: Intent on proving he's a born farmer, Dodgers takes charge of running the hydroponic space farm aboard his vessel. But to eradicate one annoying weed, Dodgers introduces a Martian cure far worse than the problem.

episodes.name: Diva Delivery
episodes.overview: Dodgers transports an intergalactic singing star, Lady Chanticleer, to the Fluoride Festival of Festoovius Five, taking tons of abuse from the perfectionist diva.

episodes.name: Castle High
episodes.overview: I.Q. Hi makes the mistake of leaving Dodgers alone with his ancestor's castle, and so Dodgers tells I.Q. Hi what happened in a Frankenstein-type exaggeration.

episodes.name: Surf the Stars
episodes.overview: When his status as Surf King on an all-beach planet is wiped out by the Crusher, Dodgers must prevail in an impossible surfing contest.

episodes.name: Samurai Quack
episodes.overview: Ingesting improperly self-prepared sushi sends Dodgers into a vivid fever dream wherein he becomes a samurai master and battles a tyrant sorcerer who bears an alarming resemblance to Dodgers' clock.

episodes.name: Of Course You Know This Means War and Peace (1)
episodes.overview: When Dodgers brings Earth and Mars to the brink of war, Dodgers betrays Cadet by letting him take the blame for Dodgers' offense, landing the young pig in space prison.

episodes.name: Of Course You Know This Means War and Peace (2)
episodes.overview: The treaty signing does not go smoothly, and Dodgers finally realizes he must restore his friendship with Cadet by clearing Cadet's name. They join forces with Marvin to capture Z9, who kidnapped the Martian Queen in a grab for power.

episodes.name: Till Doom Do Us Part
episodes.overview: A truce between Earth and Mars leaves Dodgers bored. Meanwhile, Roboto returns with a thirst for revenge as he assembles all of Dodgers' previous villains together to form the Legion of Duck Doom.

episodes.name: Villainstruck
episodes.overview: Dodgers and the Cadet go up against a hypnotist named the Magnificent Rogue, who is intent on flooding the Earth. Problems arise, however, when Rogue manages to hypnotize everyone into thinking he's the greatest, including Dodgers and Cadet.

episodes.name: Just the Two of Us
episodes.overview: The Cadet and the Centurions go on separate vacations away from their bosses.

episodes.name: The Kids Are All Wrong
episodes.overview: Dodgers and Cadet go undercover in one of earth's high schools in order to stop a martian spy from sending earth's teenagers into lunatics.

episodes.name: Win, Lose or Duck
episodes.overview: Dodgers, Cadet, Dr. I.Q. Hi, The Martian Queen, Martian Commander X-2 and a random centurion fall for an Internet scam. A random stranger forces them to fight for their lives.

episodes.name: Boar to be Riled
episodes.overview: In order to get a free rocket scooter from the Protectorate, Dodgers and the Cadet must go undercover at a rocket cycle rally on Planet Dakota. However, they immediately find out that it's actually an innocent appreciation club for rocket cycles. Now, Dodgers takes it upon himself to turn these law-abiding citizens into lawless marauders.

episodes.name: Clean Bill of Health
episodes.overview: I.Q. Hi builds a detoxification machine and uses it on Dodgers as a test subject. The machine rids Dodgers of anything impure and turns him into the perfect duck. But Dodgers' friends and enemies quickly learn they like the old Dodgers better.

episodes.name: The Best of Captains, the Worst of Captains
episodes.overview: Dodgers and Star Johnson go against each other to win the "Captain of the Year" award and the heart of a female Lieutenant.

episodes.name: That's Lifomatica
episodes.overview: Dodgers invites people to a party to celebrate his new Lifomatica, a system designed to make life easier. That is, until Lifomatica goes insane and traps the guests inside the ship.

episodes.name: Diamond Boogie
episodes.overview: Dodgers and the Cadet team up with officer Paprika Solo on Groovica to discover the location of the galaxy's missing supply of diamonds.

episodes.name: Corporate Pigfall
episodes.overview: When the Cadet quits the Protectorate to become a big corporate CEO, Dodgers decides to get him back by sabotaging his company with the help of his new Cadet, Egghead Jr.

episodes.name: The Six Wazillion Dollar Duck
episodes.overview: After being injured, Dodgers receives cyborganic parts, which give him super powers. Meanwhile, the Martian Queen and X-2 kidnap other cyborg people from Earth to steal their technology, using the dubious help of Dr. Maniac.

episodes.name: Too Close for Combat
episodes.overview: The Martian Queen hires the highly unusual assassins Hubie and Bert, who trick Dodgers and Cadet into thinking the other is out to kill them.

episodes.name: The Fins of War
episodes.overview: While on a diplomatic mission to an aquatic planet, Dodgers instigates war between the dolphin and shark people. Dodgers and Cadet are drafted to fight on opposing sides, but must find a way to bring about peace.

episodes.name: Good Duck Hunting
episodes.overview: A criminal gambling kingpin hires a gang of bounty hunters to kill Dodgers, but his plan goes downhill when one of the bounty hunters quits and offers to help Dodgers.

episodes.name: Consumption Overruled
episodes.overview: When Hungortus the Eater of Worlds heads toward the solar system for his next meal, Dodgers and the Martians hire lawyers to convince him of which planet to eat: Earth or Mars.

episodes.name: A Lame Duck Mind
episodes.overview: A psychic supervillain named Manobrain, steals top secret codes and hides them in Dodgers' brain. I.Q. Hi, Cadet, Manobrain, and embodiments of Dodgers' personality explore his mind in their quest to find them.

episodes.name: Master & Disaster
episodes.overview: A lightning-fast burglar eludes the Galactic Protectorate, forcing Dodgers and Cadet to track down an imposing Kung Fu master for assistance.

episodes.name: All in the Crime Family
episodes.overview: When a crime family corners the galaxy's chewing gum market, Dodgers and the Cadet recruit rival gangsters to fight crime with crime.

episodes.name: In Space, No One Can Hear You Rock
episodes.overview: The Martians create a weapon to drain energy from Earth's music and use its atomic power to destroy the Earth. Dodgers unfreezes Megadeth star, Dave Mustaine, to play enough heavy metal to overload the device.

episodes.name: Ridealong Calamity
episodes.overview: I.Q. Hi joins Dodgers and the Cadet for his annual ride along misadventure. Dodgers and the Cadet gradually grow tired of I.Q. Hi tagging along and they ask the Martians to fake an attack, so I.Q. Hi can save the day and leave. Unfortunately, the Martians plan to attack for real.

episodes.name: Bonafide Heroes
episodes.overview: Kirk Manlord, the host of a sleazy reality show Bonafide Heroes about universe's heroes, does a piece on Duck Dodgers. The crew follows Duck 24/7 and interviews his enemies and friends. Dodgers decides to use this opportunity to promote himself.
